FBIS4-62179 "drsov093_a_94035" FBIS-SOV-94-093 Daily Report 11 May 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Kuwait Said Planning To Buy Arms From Russia Kuwait Said Planning To Buy Arms From Russia PM1205132594 Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI in Russian 11 May 94 p 4 PM1205132594 Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI Russian BFN [Unattributed report under the "Business News" rubric: "Will We Sell Arms to Kuwait?"] [Text] The Kuwaiti Government is planning to buy military equipment in Russia, including 20 BMP-2 and 60 BMP-3 armored personnel carriers, spare parts, and possibly 27 300-mm rocket launchers. The purchase of Russian weapons represents a radical change in Kuwait's previous position; in the past, it relied solely on Western countries for the organizational development of its armed forces.
